Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and
mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces.
Trim and remove strings from @sugar snap peas{4%ounce}. Core, deseed, and dice
@bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and 1 TBSP ginger (2 TBSP for 4); cook,
stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4), and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, toss sweet potato and snap peas with a drizzle
of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon}, 1 TBSP @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon} (half the sauce
for 4 servings), salt, and @pepper{}. (You'll use more katsu sauce later.)
Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil; season with salt and
pepper. (For 4, use 2 sheets; roast sweet potatoes and snap peas on top rack
and bell peppers on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until veggies are just tender, ~{15%minutes} (they'll finish
cooking in step 5).

== Sriracha Soy Mayo ==

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
@sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and as much
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

> Start with half the Sriracha, then taste and add more from there if you like
> things spicy.

== Finishing Veggies ==

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven.
(For 4 servings, remove sheet with sweet potatoes and snap peas; leave bell
peppers roasting.) Using a #spatula{}, carefully toss sweet potato and snap peas
with half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving) and 1 TBSP
katsu sauce (remaining sauce for 4).

Return to oven until veggies are tender and sauce is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes}
more.

== Shrimp ==

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and
season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and
cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt; divide between bowls.

Arrange sweet potato and snap peas and bell pepper over top in separate sections.
Drizzle everything with as much Sriracha soy mayo as you like. Top with
scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.

Top rice with shrimp.